name: plug production, inlet and outlet, for printer cable | plug, inlet and outlet, for printer cable | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/4392/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 unit of a typical set of plugs (inlet and outlet) for a printer cable. It is based on a inlet plug with a weight of 0.0395 kg and a outlet plug of 0.050 kg. Main data are based on weighting and calculations of a Swiss type computer cable at EMPA la-boratories, supported by EPD information.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]

From reception of metal and plastic materials at the factory gate.

This dataset includes materials PVC, LDPE, HDPE, silicone, low-alloyed steel, chromium steel, brass, and copper with their respective manufacturing processes, infrastructure, electricity used in the assembly of the plugs, plus the road and rail transportation for input materials from the regional storage to the production site.
category: C:Manufacturing/26:Manufacture of computer, electronic and optical products/261:Manufacture of electronic components and boards/2610:Manufacture of electronic components and boards

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The data describes a typical set of plugs for a printer cable in 2006. Plugs and cable are produced by international manufacturers and available all over the world. Therefore a global dataset is justifiable.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The manufacturing process is inventoried through wire drawing, injection moulding, sheet rolling & hot rolling (steel), contouring (brass), and zinc coating (galvanising of steel).
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Weighing and measuring of materials. Literature for electricity consumption (assembly).

exchanges.description:
EcoSpold01Location=GLO
A printer cable refers to the cable that carries data between a computer and a printer. There are many different types of printer cables, for example: Serial, Parallel, Fire wire, USB. Parallel ports are not built in most new computers anymore, but are still part of the majority of computers currently in use. For new laptops and PCs with parallel port printers and scanners, USB adapters are available, commonly through docking stations. The key features of this specific printer cable are:
parallel printer cable for PC 
bidirectional 
Cen 36 male to DB 25 female 
length 5m 
25 cores 
connection 1:1 
long thumb screws (DB 25) 
shielded cable (foil) 
molded plugs with strain relief 
for standard printers (ink jet, laser, impact printers) 
not to use with IEEE 1284 printers (high speed EPP mode)
